# offline-budget

An analysis tool for deep dives into personal spending and budget, designed for privacy-conscious individuals. It uses only .csv bank statments downloaded from the bank and does not connect to the internet.

### Instructions for Usage

So far, this only works for .csv file statements downloaded from Chase bank or Alliant Credit Union. I'm sure Claude Code can figure out how to make it work with your .csv bank statement though.

Once you pull the repo, navigate to the root directory and run the command "docker compose up --build". This will build the jupyter container image. You can then launch jupyter by navigating to http://localhost:8888/lab in your browser.

Then, upload your .csv credit card and checking account statements into the appropriate folders in the "original_csv" directory.

Then, open the data_combining.ipynb notebook and run the cell there.

Finally, open the terminal in jupyter and run the command "python3 streamlit run src/main.py". It will then provide you a link that will open in your browser that lets you access the application.

To close it, just press CTRL+C in the Jupyter terminal, then run "docker compose down" in your machine's terminal.
